cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the aggregation of information from multiple sources, each submitting a database modelled as a first-order relational structure. This topic is closely related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as it involves knowledge representation and querying. The paper also discusses the use of social choice theory, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with integrity constraints, which are a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
